{"type":"message","id":"07fdaf7a","parentId":"1997b290","timestamp":"2026-04-26T02:56:45.257Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f6uMSTsPA9tJWkpJoR3qDHEO|fc_08960d4316f6d9700169ed7eebf4048195b9607db2d77035ed","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: gpt-image-generator\ndescription: Generate and edit images using a custom GPT responses API. Use when the user requests GPT-based image generation (text-to-image) or image editing (image-to-image).\n---\n\n# GPT Image Generator\n\nThis skill provides Python scripts to generate and edit images via a custom API endpoint.\n\n## Setup\n\nBefore using this skill, the user must configure the API URL and Key. An example configuration is provided in `references/env.example`.\n\nUsers should set these environment variables:\n- `PY_IMAGE_GEN_API_URL`\n- `PY_IMAGE_GEN_API_KEY`\n\n## Workflow\n\n### Text to Image\n\nGenerate an image from a prompt:\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/gpt-image-generator/scripts/generate_image.py \"your prompt here\"\n```\n\n### Image to Image (Edit)\n\nEdit an existing image based on a prompt:\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/gpt-image-generator/scripts/generate_image_edit.py --image <path-to-image> --prompt \"edit instructions\"\n```\n\n## Important Notes\n\n- The scripts save the generated image in the current working directory.\n- Always use the `message` tool to send the generated image back to the user immediately after success.\n- If editing, always pass the absolute path of the user's latest provided image to `--image`.\n- You can pass `--out-base <name>` to customize the output file prefix.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777172205191}}
